## Cypress Fixtures Overview

Fixtures are external data files that provide static test data for your Cypress tests. They help separate test data from test logic, making tests more maintainable and readable.

## Implementation Details

- Fixtures are stored in the `cypress/fixtures/` directory by default
- Support JSON, JS, and other file formats
- Can be loaded using `cy.fixture()` command
- Data is cached during test runs for performance

## Code Example

```javascript
// cypress/fixtures/user-data.json
{
  "name": "John Doe",
  "email": "john@example.com"
}

// cypress/component/UserComponent.spec.js
describe('UserComponent', () => {
  beforeEach(() => {
    cy.fixture('user-data').as('userData')
  })

  it('displays user information', function() {
    cy.mount(UserComponent, { props: { user: this.userData } })
    cy.get('[data-cy=user-name]').should('contain', 'John Doe')
  })
})
```

## Common Pitfalls

- Using `function() {}` instead of arrow functions to access fixture data via `this`
- Not properly handling async fixture loading
- Storing sensitive data in fixtures (use environment variables instead)
